== Ginger-Lime Rice ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger
and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Miso Peach Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork if preferred.

== Green Beans ==

While chicken cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Pan Sauce ==

Return pan used for chicken to medium heat. Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, garlic,
and remaining ginger. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 1/4 cup water, @peach jam{1}, and @miso sauce concentrate{1}. Cook, stirring, until
thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{2%tablespoon} until melted. Stir in a squeeze
of lime juice to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and a pinch of salt if necessary.

Divide rice, chicken, and green beans between #plates{}. Drizzle chicken with sauce and
serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.